                "aonid": 540,
                "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                "monster_family": {
                    "name": "Martial Artist",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "monster_family",
                    "subtypes": [
                        {
                            "name": "Alternate Moves",
                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                            "subtype": "monster_family",
                            "text": "Martial artists rarely have the same repertoire. For variety, use the following table to tweak an NPC's stats: \n\n|  |  |  |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **NPC** | **Ability** | **Replace With** |\n| Martial Student |  Fancy Footwork |  Hi-yah! |\n| Tournament Combatant |  Work the Crowd  | Competitive Taunt |\n| Mixed Martial Artist  | Any Stance Shift option  | Constant Feint Stance |\n| Black Belt |  Blocking Counterattack  | Defensive Side Kick |\n| Grandmaster |  One-Millimeter Punch | Blazing Gate |",
                            "changes": [
                                {
                                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                                    "subtype": "change",
                                    "text": "Alternate Moves",
                                    "change_category": "abilities",
                                    "abilities": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Blazing Gate",
                                            "text": "[two-actions]  (electricity)"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Requirements",
                                            "text": "The grandmaster has a target grappled or restrained;"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Effect",
                                            "text": "The grandmaster tosses their target upwards and electrocutes them with a qi-infused double palm strike as they land. The target becomes prone, loses the grappled or restrained condition, and takes 5d6 bludgeoning damage and 2d8 persistent electricity damage (DC 38 basic Fortitude save)."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Competitive Taunt",
                                            "text": "[one-action]  (emotion, fear, mental) The tournament combatant attempts to Demoralize a target. On a success, the demoralized creature is off-guard until the end of their next turn. The tournament combatant gets a +2 circumstance bonus to their damage against a creature made off-guard in this way."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Constant Feint Stance",
                                            "text": "This stance option replaces a different Stance Shift option (usually Secure Grapple Stance). +2 to attempts to Feint. If the mixed martial artist rolls a critical failure to Feint, they get a failure instead. If they successfully Feint, they can use Stance Shift as a free action. Unlike other stances, in this stance the mixed martial artist can't make Strikes."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Defensive Side Kick",
                                            "text": "[reaction]"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Trigger",
                                            "text": "A creature within the black belt's reach uses a move action;"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Effect",
                                            "text": "The black belt makes a fist Strike designed to intercept and create distance. This Strike does not count towards the black belt's multiple attack penalty, and the black belt's multiple attack penalty doesn't apply to this Strike. On a successful hit, the target is pushed 5 feet away."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Kiai!",
                                            "text": "[free-action]"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Frequency",
                                            "text": "once per turn;"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Requirements",
                                            "text": "The martial student attempts a Strike;"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Effect",
                                            "text": "The martial student shouts to startle their adversary. If the Strike is successful, the target becomes frightened 1."
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "effects": [
                                        {
                                            "target": "$.defense.automatic_abilities",
                                            "operation": "add_items",
                                            "source": "$.monster_family.subtypes[*].changes[*].abilities"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "Dirty Fighting",
                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                            "subtype": "monster_family",
                            "text": "Sometimes it doesn't pay to fight fair. You can give one of these dirty fighting tactics to any martial artist NPC. While tournament combatants are especially likely to look for an edge that will let them win, most black belts and grandmasters are unlikely to stoop to such chicanery.",
                            "changes": [
                                {
                                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                                    "subtype": "change",
                                    "text": "Dirty Fighting",
                                    "change_category": "abilities",
                                    "abilities": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Concealed Spikes",
                                            "text": "[reaction]"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Trigger",
                                            "text": "The martial artist critically succeeds on an unarmed Strike;"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Effect",
                                            "text": "Tiny spikes in the martial artist's gloves or footwear deal an additional 1d6 persistent bleed damage."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Contraband Substance",
                                            "text": "[one-action]  The martial artist pulls out a concealed alchemical vial of mutagen and drinks it to improve their combat prowess. The item is usually a juggernaut mutagen, or quicksilver mutagen. This ability can't be used again until the martial artist has time to acquire and hide a new mutagen. Some martial artists use concealed small vials, but others hide a syringe or soak the alchemical liquid into a garment they can put in their mouth."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Illegal Bite",
                                            "text": "[one-action]  The martial artist makes an Athletics check against a target's Fortitude DC to bite them in a vulnerable area. On a success, the martial artist deals 2d6 piercing damage (or double on a critical success)."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Sand In Your Eye",
                                            "text": "[one-action]  (visual) The martial artist Feints. On a success, the martial artist tosses sand into the face of one target, blinding them for 1 round or until the target Interacts to remove the blinded condition."
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "effects": [
                                        {
                                            "target": "$.defense.automatic_abilities",
                                            "operation": "add_items",
                                            "source": "$.monster_family.subtypes[*].changes[*].abilities"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "Grandmaster Forbidden Knowledge",
                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                            "subtype": "monster_family",
                            "text": "Grandmasters study techniques outlawed for their tendency to maim both the user and the victim. If the Forbidden Palm doesn't suit your grandmaster's style, swap it for one of the following moves\u2014if you dare.",
                            "changes": [
                                {
                                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                                    "subtype": "change",
                                    "text": "Grandmaster Forbidden Knowledge",
                                    "change_category": "abilities",
                                    "abilities": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Life Burn Aura",
                                            "text": "[three-actions]  (aura, force) The grandmaster transmutes their lifespan into an expulsion of qi. For the next minute, the grandmaster is surrounded by a 30-foot emanation that deals 3d6 force damage to all creatures who start their turn within the emanation, including the grandmaster themself. While Life Burn Aura is active, the grandmaster's fist Strikes deal 2 additional die of weapon damage. When the aura disappears, the grandmaster is permanently doomed 1. This condition is cumulative."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Solar Surge",
                                            "text": "[three-actions]  (visual) The grandmaster unleashes a qi wave as bright as the sun. All creatures within a 50-foot radius of the grandmaster who can see must attempt a DC 38 Reflex save, including the grandmaster themself."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Critical Success",
                                            "text": "The creature is dazzled for 1 round."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Success",
                                            "text": "The creature is blinded for 1 round."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Failure",
                                            "text": "The creature is blinded for 1 day."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Critical Failure",
                                            "text": "The creature is permanently blinded."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                                            "subtype": "ability",
                                            "name": "Super Qi Blast",
                                            "text": "[one-action] (force, spellshape, polymorph); The grandmaster's body expands as it prepares to exude an unfathomable amount of qi. If the grandmaster's next action is to cast the two-action version of *qi blast* , the size of the cone increases to 120 feet and the damage increases to 16d6. The grandmaster also becomes one size category larger for the next minute, dealing an additional +9 damage with their melee Strikes. Additionally, the grandmaster is permanently drained 1. This drained condition is cumulative."
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "effects": [
                                        {
                                            "target": "$.defense.automatic_abilities",
                                            "operation": "add_items",
                                            "source": "$.monster_family.subtypes[*].changes[*].abilities"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
